The article discusses the upcoming Major Economies Forum on Energy and Climate leaders' meeting hosted by President Biden. The meeting aims to advance climate action and energy security in key sectors such as energy, transportation, and agriculture. The President will make announcements and take actions in these sectors, including efforts to reduce methane emissions, promote clean technologies, and accelerate the adoption of zero-emission vehicles. The meeting will involve the participation of major economies and countries key to the initiatives. However, specific details on the countries attending and their commitments have not been disclosed yet. The article also mentions that the recent invasion of Ukraine by Russia has underscored the urgency of these efforts and the need to address energy and food security. The discussion also touches upon the relationship with China and the ongoing engagement on climate issues, including methane reduction. The meeting will not specifically address funding for loss and damage in developing countries, but an initiative on adaptation in Africa will be announced.